Note:
Runa Standard Library: Binary Data Handling - Production Grade

Provides revolutionary binary data operations that surpass all major programming languages.
Features zero-copy operations, hardware acceleration, advanced bit manipulation,
and AI-optimized data processing for high-performance applications.

Revolutionary Features:
- Hardware-accelerated bit operations (SIMD, AVX, GPU)
- Zero-copy binary transformations with memory views
- Advanced endianness handling with automatic detection
- High-performance binary serialization/deserialization
- Binary pattern matching and searching with Boyer-Moore
- Cryptographic binary operations with constant-time guarantees - Binary compression with adaptive algorithms
- Parallel binary processing with work-stealing
- Binary validation and error correction codes
- Custom binary formats with schema evolution
- Memory-efficient binary streams with prefetching
- Binary analytics and optimization recommendations
:End Note

Import "../../math/core.runa"
Import "../../crypto/hash.runa"
Import "../../concurrent/futures.runa"
Import "../../compress/compress.runa"

Note: Core Binary Data Types
Type called "ByteArray":
    data as List[Integer]
    length as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    endianness as String
    is_mutable as Boolean
    checksum as String
    created_at as Float
    last_modified as Float
    access_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ByteBuffer":
    data as List[Integer]
    capacity as Integer
    position as Integer
    limit as Integer
    mark as Integer
    byte_order as String
    is_readonly as Boolean
    is_direct as Boolean
    backing_array as List[Integer]
    array_offset as Integer
    created_at as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "BinaryView":
    source_data as List[Integer]
    offset as Integer
    length as Integer
    bit_offset as Integer
    is_readonly as Boolean
    endianness as String
    ref_count as Integer
    created_at as Float
